Document: XRTracker
Path: godot/classes/class_xrtracker.rst
Summary: Properties and methods for configuring XRTracker description, name, and type attributes.

Property: description (String) = ""
- Method: set_tracker_desc(value: String) → void
- Method: get_tracker_desc() → String
The description of this tracker.

Property: name (StringName) = "Unknown"
- Method: set_tracker_name(value: StringName) → void
- Method: get_tracker_name() → StringName
The unique name of this tracker. Godot expects XRInterface to implement specific reserved names:
- "head" identifies XRPositionalTracker for the player's head
- "left_hand" identifies XRControllerTracker in the player's left hand
- "right_hand" identifies XRControllerTracker in the player's right hand
- "/user/hand_tracker/left" identifies XRHandTracker for the player's left hand
- "/user/hand_tracker/right" identifies XRHandTracker for the player's right hand
- "/user/body_tracker" identifies XRBodyTracker for the player's body
- "/user/face_tracker" identifies XRFaceTracker for the player's face

Property: type (TrackerType) = 128
- Method: set_tracker_type(value: TrackerType) → void
- Method: get_tracker_type() → TrackerType
The type of tracker.